body:
Thanks @goldsborough.

when using 
std::vector<torch::jit::IValue> inputs;
inputs.push_back(torch::ones({1, 3, 224, 224}));
inputs.to(at::kCUDA);
an error occurs, 
'class std::vector<c10:IValue, std::allocator<c10::IValue>>' has no member named 'to'

Later I follow your guidance in https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/12506, and 
add tensor_image.to(at::kCUDA). It worked. Thanks!
